│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure in                │
│ ScopedHashTableScope destructor indicating a scope imbalance. This typically  │
│ happens when the key being managed in the scoped hash table is considered     │
│ equal incorrectly (violating DenseMap invariants), leading to corruption in   │
│ the table's internal TopLevelMap. Your reproducer uses 'icmp samesign', a new │
│ ICmp flag. EarlyCSE's value numbering and CSE logic relies heavily on         │
│ DenseMapInfo<SimpleValue>::getHashValue and isEqual. If those functions       │
│ consider two differing instructions equal or hash them inconsistently, the    │
│ scoped hash table can be corrupted, and popping scopes may assert.\n\n2.      │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug-only output shows EarlyCSE simplifying ashr 0 │
│ -> 0, then performing a CSE of '%icmp' to '%icmp.samesign'. That means        │
│ EarlyCSE believes an icmp with samesign flag is equivalent to one without it  │
│ and replaces the non-samesign compare with the samesign one. This is          │
│ suspicious because 'samesign' changes semantics for relational predicates.    │
│ The final simplify of add to select based on %icmp.samesign further confirms  │
│ that EarlyCSE treats them interchangeably.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn     │
│ EarlyCSE.cpp:\n- Hashing: getHashValueImpl for CmpInst hashes only the base   │
│ predicate (CI->getPredicate()) and operands. It ignores the hasSameSign       │
│ bit.\n- Equality: isEqualImpl for CmpInst uses isIdenticalToWhenDefined first │
│ (which would catch samesign differences), but then has a commuted-equality    │
│ fallback that compares swapped predicate equality and operands without taking │
│ 'hasSameSign' into account. As a result, two ICmps that differ only in        │
│ samesign may be considered equal under the commuted-equality path. Because    │
│ hashing also ignores samesign, we can end up replacing a plain icmp with a    │
│ samesign icmp (observed in the log), which is incorrect. Moreover, such       │
│ incorrect replacements and map entries can cause the scoped hash table to     │
